{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This family contains transmembrane signal transduction proteins involved in Fe2+ dicitrate sensing. Experimentally characterised members include Escherichia coli FecR [[cite:PUB00015914]] and Pseudomonas putida PupR [[cite:PUB00015986]]. Members of this family are a distinct group of anti-sigma factors [[cite:PUB00016055]].</p>\r\n<p>In E. coli, binding of ferric citrate to the outer membrane receptor/transporter protein FecA initiates a signal that is transmitted by FecR across the cytoplasmic membrane into the cytoplasm where FecI, the sigma factor, is activated [[cite:PUB00062354]]. The periplasmic N terminus of FecA interacts with the periplasmic C-terminal portion of FecR, then FecR transmits the signal across the membrane, and the cytoplasmic N terminus of FecR interacts with FecI, which results in FecI activation [[cite:PUB00016040], [cite:PUB00016138], [cite:PUB00016011]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "6ovm", "name" "Crystal Structure of the Pseudomonas capeferrum Anti-sigma Regulator PupR C-terminal Cell-surface Signaling Domain in Complex with the Outer Membrane Transporter PupB N-terminal Signaling Domain (SeMet)"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR30273" "PERIPLASMIC SIGNAL SENSOR AND SIGMA FACTOR ACTIVATOR FECR-RELATED"}, "pirsf" {"PIRSF018266" "Fe(2+)-dicitrate sensor, transmembrane component"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Fe(2+)-dicitrate sensor, transmembrane component", "short" "Ferrdict_sens_TM"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 4, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 2204, "taxa" 9741, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 63638, "sets" 0, "proteins" 63229, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 50991}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR012373", :literature {"PUB00015914" {"URL" nil, "is